# Vidsync

A React Native (Expo) application for capturing video recordings, storing metadata locally, and reliably synchronizing recordings to cloud storage using presigned S3 uploads.

The project demonstrates mobile video capture, offline-first queue processing, SQLite persistence, retry handling, and AWS infrastructure design patterns commonly used in production telemetry and media ingestion systems.

---

## Features

### Authentication

- Email-based mock login
- Session persistence across app restarts
- Secure credential storage using Expo SecureStore

### Video Capture

- Start/stop video recording
- Front/rear camera switching
- Recording timer
- Automatic save after recording completes
- Metadata collection per recording

### Local Persistence

- SQLite database via Expo SQLite
- Offline-first architecture
- Persistent upload queue
- Retry tracking and upload state management

### Upload & Sync Engine

- Presigned URL upload flow
- Persistent queue across app restarts
- Exponential retry backoff
- Upload state tracking
- Idempotent uploads using video_id

### Video Dashboard

- Paginated video listing
- Upload status indicators
- Retry failed uploads
- Delete local recordings

---

# Architecture

```text
Camera
   │
   ▼
Local File Storage
   │
   ▼
SQLite Metadata Store
   │
   ▼
Upload Queue
   │
   ▼
Backend API
   │
   ▼
Presigned URL
   │
   ▼
Amazon S3
```

Recording data is first persisted locally before any upload attempt occurs. This guarantees recordings survive app crashes, network outages, and device restarts.

